    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fighting the Taliban</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bill Mares letter holds that US should divert 'surge' troops bound for Iraq and send them to Afghanistan to fight Taliban, again</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Defense Secretary Robert M. Gates says he's sympathetic to sending more soldiers to Afghanistan (''Gates Backs Generals' Afghan Distress Call,'' news article, Jan. 18).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Defense Secretary Robert M. Gates says he's sympathetic to sending more soldiers to Afghanistan (''Gates Backs Generals' Afghan Distress Call,'' news article, Jan. 18).</p>
        <p>I am, too. He could get them by diverting the ''surge'' troops bound for the bloody follies of Iraq to fight the Taliban (again) in a war that is still winnable.</p>
        <p>Bill Mares  Burlington, Vt., Jan. 18, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
